        "created_at": "2025-02-25T14:08:14.560Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hey everyone,</p>\n<p>I‚Äôve noticed that Signal currently doesn‚Äôt support automatic formatting for bullet point lists, unlike WhatsApp. In WhatsApp, using <code>-</code>, <code>*</code>, or <code>1.</code> at the beginning of a line automatically creates a structured list, which improves readability.</p>\n<p>I‚Äôd love to see this feature in Signal as well, so that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>-</code> or <code>*</code> at the start of a line automatically turns into a bullet point</li>\n<li><code>1.</code>, <code>2.</code>, etc., are recognized as numbered lists</li>\n<li>Maybe even indentation for subpoints could be supported</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This would be super useful for notes, shopping lists, or sharing structured information.</p>\n<p>What do you think? Would this be a valuable addition to Signal?</p>\n<p>Best regards!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2025-02-25T14:55:01.343Z",
