        "created_at": "2025-02-25T14:55:39.037Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Fits this existing request:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"9731\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/34f0e0/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/todo-or-check-list/9731\">Todo or Check list</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    For the last days, I realized that my wife is using my whatsapp profile as a note reminder. She wrote shopping list and send it to me as a message. I mean it is a good way to remember smth other than Calendar. Calendar is smth people dont really use it. If they are not in any business or eager to use it personally. \nThen, a timed message with the option check marks can be very fancy. For example, in order to send a message to my wife as a list, I can send a message to myself and create a timed m‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
