        "created_at": "2025-02-25T19:23:46.293Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There‚Äôs already a request for markdown. This topic may be a duplicate.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"55358\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/melkster/48/29312_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/markdown-syntax-for-text-formatting/55358\">Markdown syntax for text formatting</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    So text formatting has been added to Signal, which was discussed <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/font-styling-for-signal-messages/612\">here</a>. However, text formatting is done through highlighting the text and clicking around in a menu. As the original request actually asks for, it would be great if it were possible to use Markdown styling for formatting the text. Here‚Äôs an example from the original feature request: \n*Italic*\n_Italic_\n**Bold**\n__Bold__\n~Strike through~\n``*Escaped not italic*``\n```*Escaped not italic*```\n\nIn my opinion this is way more useful than ha‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
